  <refnamediv>
    <refname>immean2</refname>
    <refpurpose>Average/mean of matrix elements</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Syntax</title>
   <synopsis>
   m = immean2(im)

   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>im :</term>
            <listitem><para> An image, which can be integer or double matrix, but must be one channel image.</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
            <term>m :</term>
            <listitem><para> The mean of the values in im , a scalar of class double.</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
immean2 computes the mean of a matrix using mean(im(:)).
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

